   <body class="c4">
      <p class="c0"><span class="c2 c1 c6">The Red Directory &ndash; FAQ</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c2 c1">What is the Red Directory?</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">The Red Directory is a network that looks to connect members of the HIV/AIDS community. It is a safe place for anyone involved in the community to come together and share ideas and personal thoughts. Additionally, you can search users, organizations, and events going on in the community.</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c2 c1">Who can sign up to have a profile in the Red Directory?</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">Anyone can sign up for the Red Directory. It&rsquo;s to your discretion how you use the Red Directory.</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c2 c1">Do I have to register in order to use the Red Directory?</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">Yes. To ensure safety and security to all members, you must registration is required to access any functions on the Red Directory, so you must sign up and make a profile.</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c2 c1">How do I sign up for the Red Directory?</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">It&rsquo;s easy. Just follow this link:</span><span class="c1"><a class="c5" href="https://www.google.com/url?q=http://laravelapp-oberfeld.apps.unc.edu/auth/register&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNF9C4A6qUNsCp9uIJQ8r1xl0Ipy5w">&nbsp;</a></span><span class="c1 c7"><a class="c5" href="https://www.google.com/url?q=http://laravelapp-oberfeld.apps.unc.edu/auth/register&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNF9C4A6qUNsCp9uIJQ8r1xl0Ipy5w">http://laravelapp-oberfeld.apps.unc.edu/auth/register</a></span><span class="c1">&nbsp;and fill in the fields. Finish up and you have a profile. Welcome to the Red Directory!</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1 c2">What are the requirements when I sign up?</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">When you register, you need to choose a username, supply an email address, first name, last name, and password. Optional requirements are City, State, Country, and your connection to the HIV/AIDS community.</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c2 c1">I signed up, so now what can I do?</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">Welcome to the Red Directory! Once you register or login, you will be greeted with your personal profile. This is your home page.</span></p>
      <p class="c0 c3"><span class="c1"></span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">The menu bar on top is general navigation, allowing you to access all users, all organizations, and all events, as well as search for them. Clicking Red Directory in the top left will always bring you back to your home page and clicking Log Out on the top right will log you out and take you to the launch screen.</span></p>
      <p class="c0 c3"><span class="c1"></span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">The black side bar on the left is your personal menu. Here, you can navigate to your posts, connections, organizations, and events pages. You will see your username at the top, and clicking that will also bring you back to your profile and homepage.</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c2 c1">How do I make a post?</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">To make a personal post, select the My Posts tab on the sidebar. Under the Write New Post section, type up your post and click create post. Congratulations! You&rsquo;ve created your first post! It should show up in the section above.</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c2 c1">How do I view other people&rsquo;s posts?</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">To see other people&rsquo;s posts that you&rsquo;ve connected to, select the My Posts tab on the right sidebar. The posts of people you&rsquo;ve connected with and organizations you follow will be displayed in the top section.</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">Note that you cannot see a person&rsquo;s post until you are connected to them. To connect to someone, see below.</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c2 c1">How do I connect with someone?</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">Find that user (by searching or browsing the directory &ndash; see below) and click on their hyperlinked username. This brings up their profile and from there, click the send request button. As soon as they accept your request, you will be able to see their content and they will be able to see yours.</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c2 c1">How do I accept a connection request?</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">Select the My Connections tab on the sidebar. On the right side of the content window, their connection request will show up and you will be given the option to either accept or decline.</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c2 c1">How do I search for a person?</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">In the menu bar above, select Users and browse for who you&rsquo;re looking for. Alternatively, use the search box in the top menu bar.</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c2 c1">How do I search for an organization?</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">In the menu bar above, select Organizations and browse for who you&rsquo;re looking for. Alternatively, use the search box in the top menu bar.</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c2 c1">How do I create an event?</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">Select the My Events tab on the right and scroll to the Write New Event section underneath the calendar. Fill in the appropriate event fields and click Submit Event. You&rsquo;ve created a new event! It can now be seen on the calendar above.</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c2 c1">How do I see other events that are happening?</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">Select the My Events tab on the right sidebar and all events should appear on the calendar. Use the Previous and Next buttons to navigate the months. This shows the events of the people and organizations you are following.</span></p>
      <p class="c0 c3"><span class="c1"></span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">Alternatively, clicking the Events tab on the top menu bar brings up a calendar with all events.</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c2 c1">How do I get more information on an event?</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">Just click on the event in the calendar and it will pull up the event details.</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c2 c1">How do I create an organization?</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">Select the My Organizations tab on the sidebar, then fill in the required fields and click submit. Congratulations! You&rsquo;ve created an organization!</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c2 c1">How do I post as an organization?</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">To post as an organization, select the My Posts tab on the right sidebar. Then under Write New Post, type up your post and select the appropriate profile to post under.</span></p>
      <p class="c0 c3"><span class="c1"></span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">Alternatively, select the settings tab at the top right corner in the My Organizations tab on the sidebar. There, you&rsquo;re given the option to Become the organization. After clicking this, you will effectively be logged in as that organization and can then make posts as well as events.</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c2 c1">How do I log out?</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">On the top menu bar, click Logout in the upper right hand corner.</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c2 c1">How do I delete my profile?</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">On your profile page, click the Settings button on the top right corner of the page, then confirm your profile deletion.</span></p>
      <p class="c0"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p>
      <p class="c0 c3"><span class="c1"></span></p>
   </body>
